"""Manage SNAPSHOTS and embedded markdown in gas-price-breakdown.html.

Subcommands:
  list-snapshots HTML
      Print one line per snapshot: date, state count, notes preview.

  add-snapshot HTML [--target DATE] [--baseline DATE] [--dry-run]
      Fetch live data and append a snapshot for DATE (default: most recent
      Thursday). Inherits state-tax structure (cols 3-4) from the BASELINE
      snapshot; does not refresh state tax rates -- those need human review.

  remove-snapshot HTML SNAPSHOT_DATE [--dry-run]
      Remove the snapshot whose `date` field is SNAPSHOT_DATE.

  extract-markdown HTML [--output PATH]
      Write the embedded SPEC_MD spec text to PATH (or stdout).

Data sources used by add-snapshot:
  Fetched live: AAA state-averages (retail), CARB weekly LCFS xlsx,
  Oregon DEQ CFP credit-transfer xlsx.

  Hand-maintained tables (need quarterly human update): CARB cap-and-trade
  auction settlements (CARB_CCA_AUCTIONS), Washington CCA auction
  settlements (WA_CCA_AUCTIONS). The script logs a warning when an entry
  is older than CCA_STALE_DAYS.
"""

